               <idno type="FIEY">242</idno>
               <idno type="BHSYRE">882</idno>
               <sex value="M" source="#bibl826-1">male</sex>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl826-1">Liber castitatis, n° 127. Vie "jacobite" plus nkente : Rahmani, Studia syriaca, I, 33- 34; BHO, 510. R. Beulay, "Precisions touchant l'identite et Ia biographie de Jean Saba de Dalyatha", PdO 8 (1977- 78), 87-116, et les differents ouvrages du meme auteur sur Ia doctrine spirituelle du moine ; idem, L 'enseignement spirituel de Jean de Dalyatha (Paris, 1990). BSO, I, 1122- 23 (J. Rabbi).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">John of Dalyatha was a famous spiritual author also called John Saba.  He was a monk of the monastery of Mar Yozadaq in Qardu. His writings were condemned under the Synod of Timothy I, but they were rehabilitated by Isho bar Nun. </note>
